analysis_findings.key_insight: Large N uses sophisticated tessellation with ~68°/248° angles. Small N are already optimal. Medium N (21-50) has diverse angles - not simple tessellation.

conclusion: The baseline uses a sophisticated asymmetric configuration that is already near-optimal. Small N (1-10) are provably optimal. Large N (100+) use efficient tessellation. The gap to target (1.708) cannot be closed by optimizing within this structure.
